  h1 Getting the assets

  p.
    There are two easy ways to get started with the style guide. Each of them requires you to download the archive from above.

  p.
    You can use the compiled CSS and JavaScript or you can use the source LESS and CoffeScript.
    We recommend using the source files since it provides you much more flexibility.

.l-row
  .l-half
    h2 Using the compiled CSS and JavaScript
    p.
      Copy the css/, js/, images/ and fonts/ folder from the downloaded style guide release to your project and use it as you like. See the "Basic template" section for further information.
    p.note.
      Note that the resources must be available from the web
      in the same hierarchy as provided by the style guide.
      (For example the images/ folder has to be in the same location
      as the css/ folder since images are referenced in the css files using a prefix of ../images/).

  .l-half
    h2 Using the source files (LESS, CoffeScript)
    p.
      Compiling the source files on your own is a little trickier than using the compiled CSS and JavaScript but provides you with much more flexibility.

    h3 Compiling the LESS files
    p.
      To have the flexibility of customizing LESS variables of the style guide (see section TODO) and use the provided mixins you may want to include the LESS files into your applications LESS file.

    p.
      You could also compile the style guide on its own, but that would not make any sense since you could use the compiled version in this case. For instructions on building the style guide on its own see the README.md file.

    p.callout
      | We recommend using the official LESS compiler provided at
      != ' '
      a(href='http://lesscss.org') lesscss.org
      != ' '
      | since the style guide is tested with this compiler.

    h3 Compiling the CoffeeScript files
    p.
      Since you do not gain anything by compiling the CoffeeScript files on your own we do not recommend it. Simply use the JavaScript files provided.

    h3 Copying the other assets
    p.
      Make sure to copy the assets from the images/ and fonts/ folder to a location available from the web. See the section "Compiling the LESS files" on how to set the URL root for assets.

